The paper discusses multi-agent planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that deals with the coordination of multiple agents to achieve a common goal. The paper also focuses on the conditions that require cooperation between agents, which falls under the subfield of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper uses formal analysis and mathematical models to establish its results, which is a characteristic of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the application of its findings in human-robot teaming, which falls under the subfield of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY).
